02/03/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- By a vote of 77-19, the Yugoslav Federal Parliament approved Friday (28 February) the charter on human and minority rights. Its adoption was the last remaining condition before formation of the new Serbia-Montenegro federation. The first session of the new parliament will take place Monday.
Meanwhile, local sources report that Svetozar Marovic, vice president of Montenegro's ruling Democratic Party of Socialists (DPS), will be elected president of the new federation Tuesday. The Serbian daily <I>Blic</I> reports that Serbia's ruling Democratic Opposition of Serbia and DPS have largely agreed on the future cabinet. (Blic, Tanjug, B92, FoNet - 01/03/03)
